Ques:-

An application currently running on the Kubernetes cluster employs the nginx web server. The Nautilus application development team has introduced some recent changes that need deployment. They've crafted an image nginx:1.18 with the latest updates.
Execute a rolling update for this application, integrating the nginx:1.18 image. The deployment is named nginx-deployment.
Ensure all pods are operational post-update.



Soln:-

Step 1: Check if the existing Deployment and the existing Pods are active and running or not

kubectl get deploy
kubectl get pods



Step 2: Describe a running existing Pod

kubectl describe pods <pod name> (check for the current version of the image running inside the container using the describe command)



Step 3: Update the version of the Image (We have to use set image command with deployment name and container name)

kubectl set image deployments/<deployment name> <container name>=<new image version>



Step 4: Rollout Restart the Deployment

kubectl rollout restart deployments/<deployment name>



Step 5: Let's verify the rollout status

kubectl rollout status deployments/<deployment name>



Step 6: Verification

kubectl get pods
kubectl describe pods <pod name> (check and verify for the new version of the image)
